    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-29T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-29T07:00:00-05:00" n="113"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/41: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="from"
                            >Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-29T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 29, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 29—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Consulate’s 51, January 29, noon.<note n="69" xml:id="d113fn69">Not
                        printed.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> has just conveyed to me the
                    following communication with the request that it be transmitted to you: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“A meeting was held this morning between the President of the Council,
                            French representative, and the representatives of Great Britain,
                            Germany, Italy, together with the Secretary General.</p>
                        <p>The proposal was put forward that in view of the Chinese request for the
                            application of article No. 15 as well as article No. 11, a request based
                            clearly on recent developments at Shanghai, the Commission of Inquiry
                            should be asked to proceed to Shanghai by the quickest possible route,
                            the Trans-Siberian Railroad. As this, however, at best must take 3 weeks
                            it was suggested that in the meantime the powers having nationals on the
                            Commission should be invited by the Council to form a temporary
                            commission to act as a provisional commission pending arrival of the
                            Commission already nominated. The provisional commission would consist
                            of those Ministers or Consuls General on the spot and its task would be
                            to report on the facts and causes of the recent incidents at
                            Shanghai.</p>
                        <p>The representatives of France, Great Britain, Germany and Italy are
                            requesting the agreement of their Governments to this proposal. They
                            expressed the hope that if such a temporary commission is formed the
                            Minister or Consul General of the United States in Shanghai will be
                            authorized to be a member of it.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please instruct as to reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GPB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
